{"comments":"Pure PureScript implementation of SHA-512 (FIPS 180-4).\n\nThis implementation is designed for correctness and determinism, not speed.\nSHA-512 produces a 512-bit (64-byte) hash using 64-bit arithmetic.\n\n## Why Pure SHA-512?\n\nAt billion-agent scale, agents need deterministic identity with larger\ncollision resistance. SHA-512 provides 256-bit security vs SHA-256's 128-bit.\n- Same content → same hash (always)\n- No platform-specific behavior\n- No FFI edge cases\n- Full algebraic reasoning about hashes\n\n## Algorithm Overview\n\nSHA-512 processes data in 1024-bit (128-byte) blocks:\n1. Pad message to multiple of 1024 bits\n2. Initialize eight 64-bit hash values (H0-H7)\n3. For each block: expand to 80 words, apply 80 rounds of mixing\n4. Output final 512-bit (64-byte) hash\n\n## 64-bit Arithmetic in PureScript\n\nPureScript integers are 32-bit. We represent 64-bit words as pairs of\n32-bit integers: { hi :: Int, lo :: Int } where hi is the upper 32 bits\nand lo is the lower 32 bits.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA512"],"SHA512Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[187,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA512.purs","start":[187,1]},"title":"eqSHA512Hash"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA512"],"SHA512Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[190,25],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA512.purs","start":[189,1]},"title":"showSHA512Hash"}],"comments":"A SHA-512 hash — 512 bits represented as eight 64-bit words.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[185,47],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA512.purs","start":[185,1]},"title":"SHA512Hash"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute SHA-512 hash of a string (UTF-8 encoded as ASCII bytes)\n\nNote: This assumes ASCII input. For full UTF-8 support, use sha512Bytes\nwith proper UTF-8 encoding.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA512"],"SHA512Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[576,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA512.purs","start":[576,1]},"title":"sha512"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute SHA-512 hash of byte array\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA512"],"SHA512Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[539,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA512.purs","start":[539,1]},"title":"sha512Bytes"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute SHA-512 and return hex string directly\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag"